    "recap_headline": "University of Louisville Athletics",
    "recap_text": "LOUISVILLE, Ky. \u2013\nThe University of Louisville baseball team outlasted Notre Dame in a 21-12 shootout on a windy Sunday at Jim Patterson Stadium.\nLouisville (14-6, 2-1 ACC) rebounded after losing Friday's opener to win the final two games of the weekend and the series. The Cardinals have won nine of their 11 opening weekends of ACC play.\nWith the wind howling on Sunday, it was all about the offense.\nBen Slanker\ngot the scoring started with a three-run homer in the second inning, his fourth of the week.\nNotre Dame (11-6, 3-3) immediately responded with a three-run homer of its own in the third and then grabbed the lead with a two-run shot later in the inning.\nTague Davis\ndoubled home\nAlex Alicea\nto get the Cards on the board in the bottom half of the third before Slanker delivered his second three-run swing of the day. With the bases loaded, the junior lined a ball into the right field corner to score all three runs and put the Cardinals back in front.\nThe back-and-forth continued in the fourth, with the Irish grabbing the lead back on a grand slam. Louisville's answer came via a two-run single from Davis to tie up the score at nine.\nKian Vorster\ncame on and worked a scoreless fifth and the Cardinals capitalized in their half.\nJimmy Nugent\nhammered a ball over the berm in left field to push the Cards back in front. A throwing error and sac fly pushed two more runs home before\nGriffin Crain\nlaunched a two-run shot to right-center to make it a 14-9 contest.\nNotre Dame plated three runs in the sixth, but Louisville answered with three in the seventh and four more in the eighth to seal the win.\nCrain had run-scoring doubles in each of the seventh and eighth innings, while Nugent doubled in a pair and\nBayram Hot\nhit a towering homer inside the left field foul pole.\nAll nine Cardinals starters had at least one hit in the game. Crain was a perfect 4-for-4, reaching in all six plate appearances, scoring five times and driving in four.\nAlex Alicea\nadded four hits of his own and scored three times. Davis and Nugent drove in three apiece.\nVorster earned the first win of his career with his scoreless inning in the fifth. The combination of\nJake Schweitzer\n,\nZane Stahl\nand\nBrandon Shannon\ncombined to get the final eight outs of the game without allowing a run.\nLouisville will round out its long homestand with a non-conference game against Northern Kentucky. The game is scheduled for Tuesday at 6 p.m. ET, however the game may be moved to Wednesday due to weather.\nFOLLOW LOUISVILLE BASEBALL ON SOCIAL MEDIA\nFans can follow Louisville baseball on\nX\n,\nFacebook\nor\nInstagram\nat @LouisvilleBSB."
